    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - 5 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS SPICER ES60-5 - REASSEMBLE -
        MAINSHAFT
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="10">
        <title>MAINSHAFT</title>
        <para>Refer to
            <hotlnk document="s13012_9.xml" xrefid="f1301222">Figure 22</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Mainshaft assembly begins by placing the 1st speed gear and thrustwasher on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301244">Figure 44</hotlnk>). Secure them with a snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301244" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301244" filename="../figg13/G1301244.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 44. Mainshaft Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the 2nd speed gear on the mainshaft, over two rows of loose needle bearings (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301245">Figure 45</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301245" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301245" filename="../figg13/G1301245.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 45. 2nd Speed Gear on the Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the 2nd-3rd speed clutch gear and secure it with a snap ring (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301246">Figure 46</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301246" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301246" filename="../figg13/G1301246.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 46. 2nd - 3rd Speed Clutch Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the 2nd-3rd speed synchronizer over the clutch gear (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301247">Figure 47</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301247" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301247" filename="../figg13/G1301247.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 47. 2nd - 3rd Speed Synchronizer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Coat all fluted diameters with Moly #2 lubricant (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301248">Figure 48</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301248" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301248" filename="../figg13/G1301248.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 48. Coat Fluted Diameters</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Assemble the 3rd speed gear and thrust washer (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301249">Figure 49</hotlnk>). Secure them with a snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301249" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301249" filename="../figg13/G1301249.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 49. 3rd Speed Gear and Thrust Washer</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The 4th speed gear, complete with thrust washer, may be assembled onto the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301250">Figure 50</hotlnk>). Secure with a snap ring.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301250" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301250" filename="../figg13/G1301250.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 50. 4th Speed Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place 4th-5th speed synchronizer on the mainshaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301251">Figure 51</hotlnk>). Use a suitable driver to install the main drive gear
                pocket bearing.
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301251" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301251" filename="../figg13/G1301251.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 51. 4th - 5th Speed Synchronizer on Mainshaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Set the mainshaft on the bench. Install 1st-reverse clutch gear and reverse gear with a
                caged needle bearing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301252">Figure 52</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301252" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301252" filename="../figg13/G1301252.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 52. 1st - Reverse Clutch Gear</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">The output bearing must be firmly seated against the reverse gear/thrust washer to prevent
                the washer from moving (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301253">Figure 53</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301253" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301253" filename="../figg13/G1301253.webp" type="webp" resolution="72"/>
                <caption>Figure 53. Output Bearing Firmly Seated</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
